The preceding is a list of intents with entity slots.  The intents represent the actions available for a customer to request.   The slots represent the types of information that would be important to the processing of that customer request.  If a slot has ‘Slot Possible Values’ this indicates that only the values listed can be matched to that slot.
Your task is to match the customer inquiry below with as many intents as can be identified.  When you return the selected intents, you also need to return any relevant slots and their corresponding values. If no slot value is found, populate that slot value with “None”. If no slot is associated with a class, return the following as the slot identifier - 0aaaa0a000000aa00 and populate that slot value with “None”.
Your output should be in JSON as noted in the following example.  If there are multiple intents to be returned, then place all of them in the same json output.
 
Output example:
{
    "<intent1_id>": [
    {"slot_id": "<slot_id1>", "slot_value": "<slot_value1>"},
    {"slot_id": "<slot_id2>", "slot_value": "<slot_value2>"}
]
}
 
For the above example “<>” means the actual value (“<slot_id>” = “abc123”) while just having quotes means the literal value (“slot_id” = “slot_id”).


You need to assess: I didn’t really have a great experience with my computer hand-in.  I want to provide a suggestion on how to improve the process.
